parameters: Ceres: ...

Ceres: Luna... always cheerful, bright, and charming, but sometimes, she had
such sad eyes.

Ceres: Looking back now, maybe I saw you as a mentor... or like a reliable older
brother.

Ceres: Whether it was Jupiterino or Valentina, most countries in this world
ruled people through violence and fear. They were all the same. Luna, I've never
seen a leader like you who willingly abandoned the use of force.

Ceres: No matter how capable and excellent a person is, their character changes
once they hold power. Just like Princess Lucia. You used to tell me over and
over again, and you knew it better than anyone. Now I finally understand the
true meaning of your words. Luna...

Ceres: After the last war, I created the Knights of Messiah as the world's
police force out of my own selfishness to carry on your will... but I don't have
the power to save the people like you did.
Ceres: What should I do now... Tell me, Luna.
Ceres: ...
Ceres: Rinny...
rini-1
Rinny: ...
Rinny: Yo, were you thinking about Luna?
Ceres: Yeah... How did you know?

Rinny: Ceres, when you make that face, it's always when you're thinking about
Luna.
Rinny: What's up? Something happened?

Ceres: I was thinking about withdrawing from Jupiterino, but the people there
got angry with me. I'm not sure what to do.

Rinny: Like I told the Blue Mage Luna, making an enemy out of Valentina is
suicidal. Withdrawing from Jupiterino is the right move.
Ceres: Yeah. I think so too.

Ceres: Do you know a person named Regnus Grahardt? He seems to be the hope of
the resistance in this country.

Rinny: I've heard of him but never seen him. Even Regnus Grahardt can't stop
those from Valentina.
Ceres: Why not?

Rinny: Regnus Grahardt was defeated by Zena of Valentina. That's what the rumors
say.
Ceres: Defeated by Lord Zena... No way...

Rinny: Well... my memory is hazy on this. It was something that was passed down
orally among high-ranking mages. I haven't confirmed it myself.

Rinny: The mysterious figure known as Regnus Grahardt isn't just in Jupiterino.
He's been spotted all over the world for a long time.
Ceres: The generals of Valentina are being commanded by Lord Zena?

Rinny: That's right. You must have heard the rumors about Zena, the son of the
Queen of Valentina?
Ceres: Zena of the Forbidden Books...

Rinny: You know it well. Zena uses all kinds of forbidden books and is nearly
invincible. It makes sense that Regnus Grahardt was defeated, whoever he is.

Ceres: So the rumors about Lord Zena using a large number of forbidden books are
true. But why does Regnus Grahardt still exist if he was defeated by Zena?
Rinny: Dunno. That's beyond my knowledge.

Rinny: Even if Luna were here, our prospects would be grim. The Knights of
Messiah can't handle an opponent like this.
Ceres: ...

Rinny: After all, the Knights of Messiah are essentially a volunteer army that
interferes with other countries' internal affairs, right? It's good to carry on
Luna's will, but I think it's a job that doesn't pay off.
Ceres: You're absolutely right. I have no comeback.

Ceres: Haha... Thank you. Rinny, I'm glad I could talk to you. It's almost tear-
jerking how much you bring me back to reality.
Rinny: ...
Rinny: What are you planning to do? What's on your mind?

Ceres: Well, what to do. It won't be like when Luna was here, but I'll think of
my own way to do things... though I might end up retreating anyway... haha...

Ceres: It's cold, so go eat something. There's beef hotpot and beef bowl
available~
Rinny: Tch, mind your own business.

Ceres: Are you on a diet? Come to think of it, you've gained weight recently,
haven't you?
Rinny: I'm not! I haven't gained weight! Shut up!

Ceres: It's not so much that you've gotten fat, but rather you've developed
quite noticeably. Anyway, you'll catch a cold if you stay there. I'll be waiting
at the campsite~
Rinny: Tch... What a rude person. Not a shred of delicacy.
Rinny: ...
Rinny: Ceres, what are you planning to do?
